===subject:Political reason for Emancipation
===from:Chad-Everett Tisdale
===date:Tue Feb 11 19:10:45 2003
===message:I believe also that it would have been foolhearty to fight against the south without the goal of abolishing slavery.  However, when Lincoln issued the Emancipation Proclamation, did he do it with the goal of freeing slaves or because he felt that it was necessary to unify his political party and secure once again the nomination for president.  It may not be clear how much pressure his cabinet felt from Britain after the Trent Affair.  I would wager that his major reason for doing it was not because he felt that "it was the right thing to do."
=========yorg=========
