===message:The result of the Civil War brought many good things to the U.S.  Ending slavery, establishing a national banking system, and the promotion of large scale businesses were all advatngages.  I think that the greatest advantage of all of these was increasing federal powers.  Carla, I do dissagree with your comment about state's rights today though.  I feel like if states continued to increase their power, the United States would turn out like Europe--each state having their own laws and eventually becoming their own country.  That is why we are called the "United" States of America.
