===subject:Reply
===from:Brenda Miller
===date:Mon Feb 17 15:32:30 2003
===message:Lincoln's issuing the Emancipation Proclamation was not geared towards freeing the slaves, it was to bring all states into line.  Slaves were to be freed in states that were in "rebellion" others were allowed to keep their slaves.  Lincoln did not abolish slavery with the Emancipation Proclamation he only used it as a measure to  bring states back into the Union.  
